        <heading>OBLIGATIONS IN GENERAL</heading>
        <content>
          <p>TITLE III.  OBLIGATIONS IN GENERAL
CHAPTER 1.  GENERAL PRINCIPLES
Art. 1756.  Obligations; definition
An obligation is a legal relationship whereby a person, called the obligor, is bound to render a performance in favor of another, called the obligee.  Performance may consist of giving, doing, or not doing something.</p>
        </content>
